<!-- Exercise 3 version 1 -->
<div name="a">  
  <p><term>Average velocity</term> on an interval is defined for a moving object with position function <m>s(t)</m>; more generally, we can consider the <term>average rate of change</term> of any function <m>f</m> on an interval <m>[a,b]</m>, which is defined by <m>AV_{[a,b]} = \frac{f(b)-f(a)}{b-a}</m>.</p>
  <p>Let <m>f(x) = 9 - x^2</m>.</p>
  <ol marker="a">
    <li>Compute each of the following average rates of change.
      <ol marker="i">
        <li><m>AV_{[0,1]} = </m><answer><award>-1</award></answer></li>
        <li><m>AV_{[1,3]} = </m><answer><award>-4</award></answer></li>
        <li><m>AV_{[0,3]} = </m><answer><award>-3</award></answer></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>Based on the graph sketched below, match each of your answers in (i)–(iii) with one of the lines labeled A–F. Type the corresponding letter of the line segment next to the appropriate formula. Not all letters will be used. </li>
    <graph xmin="-3.25" xmax="3.25" ymin="-0.5" ymax="9.5" showNavigation="False" displayXAxisTickLabels="false" displayYAxisTickLabels="false">
<!-- axis labels -->
      <number anchor="(-0.25,2)">2</number>
      <number anchor="(-0.25,4)">4</number>
      <number anchor="(-0.25,6)">6</number>
      <number anchor="(-0.25,8)">8</number>
      <number anchor="(-3,-0.25)">- 3</number>
      <number anchor="(-2,-0.25)">- 2</number>
      <number anchor="(-1,-0.25)">- 1</number>
      <number anchor="(1,-0.25)">1</number>
      <number anchor="(2,-0.25)">2</number>
      <number anchor="(3,-0.25)">3</number>
<!-- functions -->
      <function domain='[-3,3]' styleNumber="1" labelPosition="left">9 -x^2<label><m>y = f(x)</m></label></function>
      <function domain='[0,1]' styleNumber="2" applyStyleToLabel labelPosition="upperLeft">8<label><m>A</m></label></function>
      <function domain='[0,3]' styleNumber="3" labelIsName applyStyleToLabel labelPosition="right">-3x + 9<label><m>B</m></label></function>
      <function domain='[1,3]' styleNumber="4" labelIsName applyStyleToLabel labelPosition="right">-4x + 12<label><m>C</m></label></function>
      <function domain='[0,1]' styleNumber="5" labelIsName applyStyleToLabel labelPosition="left">-x + 9 <label><m>D</m></label></function>
      <function domain='[0,1]' styleNumber="6" labelIsName applyStyleToLabel labelPosition="lowerLeft">8x<label><m>E</m></label></function>
      <linesegment endpoints="(1,0) (1,8)" styleNumber="7" labelIsName labelPosition="lowerLeft" applyStyleToLabel>x=1<label><m>F</m></label></linesegment>
    </graph>
      <ol marker="i">
        <li><m>\frac{f(1) - f(0)}{1-0} = </m><answer><award>D</award></answer></li>
        <li><m>\frac{f(3) - f(1)}{3-1} = </m><answer><award>C</award></answer></li>
        <li><m>\frac{f(3) - f(0)}{3-0} = </m><answer><award>B</award></answer></li>
      </ol>
  </ol>
</div>
   
